	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cura&#231;oa</placeName> <date>April 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I am in possession of the Bible<lb/> &#36;4 at your credit and also of your short but kind<lb/> favor.  Believe me I heartily sympathize with you<lb/> and did I enjoy the pleasure of a more intimate acquaintance<lb/> would take the liberty of assisting<add>&#63;</add> you&#44; since you have been so<lb/> long and so unweariedly fighting the battles of true religion<lb/> and consistency&#44; you should now retire from the field<lb/> and you can do so with the pleasing consciousness that<lb/> you have not only diligently but successfully struggled<lb/> for the faith.  Let others now buckle on the armour.  A<lb/> man owes certain duties to himself.  The vice of modern<lb/> <add>&#63;</add>torship is to sacrifice.  Truth and Gentlemanly conduct<lb/> the smartness&#59; ably described in <persName>Bulwer&#39;s</persName> &#8220;<persName>Paul Clifford</persName>&#8221;<lb/> The synagogue has taken wide and deep roots in the <placeName>U S.</placeName><lb/> and the modern fashionable Pantheism with all<lb/> the other crazy German &#8220;Isms&#8221; will not prevail against it<lb/>  Tender our kind regards to <persName>Mr E Moses</persName> <persName>Mr<lb/> Lobo</persName> &#38; family and accept the same from yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">Henry Nathan</persName></p>
		</body>
